Date: Thu, 20 Oct 2011 14:58:23 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] memmon/ppc64: BOOK3E PPC64 should use the classic BOOKE TLB flush

Since PPC64 BOOKE has no tlb batch flush, it must use the classic booke TLB
flush methods.

Signed-off-by: Yongli He <yongli.he@windriver.com>
---
 mm/memmon.c |    2 ++
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/mm/memmon.c b/mm/memmon.c
index ddb1104..0f2c872 100644
--- a/mm/memmon.c
+++ b/mm/memmon.c
@@ -33,6 +33,7 @@
 
 
 #ifdef CONFIG_PPC64
+#ifndef CONFIG_PPC_BOOK3E
 #define BATCH_FLUSH
 static inline void flush_tlb_pending()
 {
@@ -47,6 +48,7 @@ static inline void flush_tlb_pending()
 
 	put_cpu_var(ppc64_tlb_batch);
 }
+#endif 
 #endif
 
